   <text>
      <body>
         <div lang="grc" type="textpart" subtype="section">
            <div n="i" type="textpart" subtype="section">
               <note>A board, type 3Rows.1, clear-cut graffito, with frame, central line, and circles on central line (<measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.56</measure> x <measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.77</measure>). On the south side, 2 crosses (ave. <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.055</measure>) have been cut across the frame; between them a monogram appears to have been erased. 
</note>
            </div>
            <div n="ii" type="textpart" subtype="section">
               <note>A circle, type C.7; diam. 0.53.</note>
            </div>
            <div n="iii" type="textpart" subtype="section">
               <ab>
                  <note>A circle, type C.2, very lightly cut; diam. 0.48. Across it an inscription: 
</note>
                  <lb n="1"/>
                  <w>Ἡ</w>
                  <w>τύχη</w>
                  <persName type="divine">
                     <expan>
                        <abbr>Οὐρ</abbr>
                        <supplied reason="abbreviation" cert="low">ανία</supplied>
                     </expan>
                  </persName>
               </ab>
            </div>
            <div n="iv" type="textpart" subtype="section">
               <note>A circle type C.2, very worn (diam. 0.56). 
</note>
            </div>
            <div n="v" type="textpart" subtype="section">
               <note>A circle, type C.7 (diam. 0.35). </note>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>iii: The fortune <supplied reason="abbreviation" cert="low">is</supplied> Our<supplied reason="abbreviation" cert="low">ania</supplied>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See Roueché, ‘Gameboards’.</p>
         </div>
